 {"id":"asupersync-15smp","title":"Actor E2E test suite with structured logging","description":"# Actor E2E Test Suite

## Goal

Create a comprehensive end-to-end test suite for the actor system with structured logging, covering all actor functionality in realistic scenarios.

## Test Directory Structure

```
tests/
├── actor/
│   ├── mod.rs                    # Test module root
│   ├── e2e/
│   │   ├── mod.rs
│   │   ├── basic_messaging.rs    # Simple send/receive patterns
│   │   ├── supervision_tree.rs   # Multi-level supervision
│   │   ├── backpressure.rs       # Mailbox overflow scenarios
│   │   ├── failure_recovery.rs   # Crash and restart flows
│   │   ├── graceful_shutdown.rs  # Region close with actors
│   │   └── stress.rs             # High-load scenarios
│   ├── unit/
│   │   ├── actor_id.rs           # ActorId generation/reuse
│   │   ├── actor_ref.rs          # ActorRef send/receive
│   │   ├── mailbox.rs            # Mailbox policies
│   │   ├── lifecycle.rs          # State transitions
│   │   └── supervision.rs        # Restart policies
│   └── integration/
│       ├── lab_runtime.rs        # Determinism tests
│       ├── cancellation.rs       # Cancel protocol
│       └── obligations.rs        # Obligation tracking
```

## Logging Requirements

### Structured Log Format
Every test must use structured logging via `tracing`:
```rust
use tracing::{info, warn, error, span, Level};

#[test]
fn test_actor_receives_message() {
    init_test_logging();  // From src/test_logging.rs

    let test_span = span\!(Level::INFO, 'test', name = 'actor_receives_message');
    let _guard = test_span.enter();

    info\!(phase = 'setup', 'Creating test actors');
    // ... test code ...
    info\!(phase = 'verify', messages_sent = 10, 'Verifying message delivery');
}
```

### Required Log Fields
- `phase`: setup, execute, verify, teardown
- `actor_id`: When operating on specific actor
- `message_type`: Type of message being sent
- `outcome`: Result of operations
- `duration_ms`: Timing for performance-sensitive ops

### Log Levels
- `TRACE`: Internal state transitions
- `DEBUG`: Individual message send/receive
- `INFO`: Test phase transitions, key events
- `WARN`: Unexpected but handled conditions
- `ERROR`: Failures that should fail the test

## E2E Test Scenarios

### 1. Basic Messaging (basic_messaging.rs)
