    let lab = LabRuntime::new(config);
    lab.run(|| { /* spawn actor without cleanup */ });
    assert\!(lab.actor_leak_oracle().is_err());
}
```

## Test Script Runner

Create `scripts/test_actors.sh`:
```bash
#\!/bin/bash
set -euo pipefail

LOG_DIR='./test_logs/actors'
mkdir -p '$LOG_DIR'

echo '=== Actor Unit Tests ==='
RUST_LOG=debug cargo test --test actor_unit -- --nocapture 2>&1 | tee '$LOG_DIR/unit.log'

echo '=== Actor Integration Tests ==='  
RUST_LOG=info cargo test --test actor_integration -- --nocapture 2>&1 | tee '$LOG_DIR/integration.log'

echo '=== Actor E2E Tests ==='
RUST_LOG=info cargo test --test actor_e2e -- --nocapture 2>&1 | tee '$LOG_DIR/e2e.log'

echo '=== Actor Stress Tests ==='
RUST_LOG=warn cargo test --test actor_stress --release -- --nocapture 2>&1 | tee '$LOG_DIR/stress.log'

echo 'All actor tests passed\!'
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All test files created in specified structure
- [ ] Every test uses structured logging with required fields
- [ ] Unit tests cover all public API methods
- [ ] Integration tests verify lab runtime determinism
- [ ] E2E tests cover realistic scenarios
- [ ] Stress tests verify performance under load
- [ ] Test script runs all tests with log capture
- [ ] CI integration configured
